# REST API (Orion + JWT)

## Route Organization

API routes split by domain in `routes/api/v1/`:
`auth`, `users`, `events`, `ticket-types`, `checkout`, `me`, `admin`, `volunteer`, `grants`.

> **Note:** API route registration is currently commented out in `RouteServiceProvider`. Uncomment to enable:
> ```php
> Route::middleware('api')->prefix('api/v1')->group(base_path('routes/api/v1.php'));
> ```

## Controllers

- Extend `OrionController` (top-level) or `OrionRelationsController` (nested)
- Declare `$model`, `$resource`, `$policy`, `$request` on the controller
- Override `buildIndexFetchQuery` / `buildShowFetchQuery` for custom eager loading
- Non-CRUD flows get dedicated controllers: `CheckoutController`, `AuthController`, `StripeWebhookController`, etc.

Orion route helpers: `Orion::resource()`, `Orion::hasManyResource()`, `Orion::belongsToManyResource()`.

## Form Requests

Extend `Orion\Http\Requests\Request` with `commonRules()`, `storeRules()`, `updateRules()`.

## Middleware

- `token.refresh` — `ConditionalJwtRefresh` (controlled by `JWT_REQUIRE_REFRESH`)
- `lockdown:ticket` etc. — blocks mutations during event lockdown
- `StripeWebhookMiddleware` — IP validation for Stripe webhooks

## JSON Responses

Shape output with `app/Http/Resources/` classes. Auth guard for API is `api` (JWT per `config/orion.php`).
